W3C's non-proprietary alternative to Flash and bitmapped graphics.
SVG enables 2-D resolution- and media-independent graphics in a text- based format.
This permits integration with XHTML, XSL and XSLT, XLink, SMIL, DOM and other W3 specifications... ...including complete support for CSS, scripting, and animation.
3 Object Types: Vector graphic shapes (paths consisting of straight lines and curves), Text, and Images.
